d-car-taxes-as-much-as-21-letter-123102300057_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Report%20Calls%20For%20Global%20Minimum%20Tax%20on%20Billionaires%2C%20Says%20Offshore%20Tax%20Evasion%20Has%20Decreased%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17155644%2Fimage-1399.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20new%20report%20has%20addressed%20what%20has%20really%20been%20done%20to%20curb%20tax%20evasion%2C%20globally%2C%20and%20what%20remains%20to%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20question%2C%20the%20report%20acknowledges%2C%20is%20of%20tremendous%20importance%2C%20given%20the%20rising%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%2C%20high%20public%20debt%20in%20the%20post-COVID-19%20context%2C%20and%20the%20significant%20need%20for%20government%20revenue%20to%20address%20climate%20change%20and%20fund%20essential%20services%20like%20healthcare%2C%20education%2C%20and%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Global%20Tax%20Evasion%20Report%E2%80%99%20is%20prepared%20by%20the%20EU%20Tax%20Observatory%2C%20a%20research%20laboratory%20established%20in%202021%20with%20expertise%20in%20international%20tax%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20edition%20of%20the%20report.%20It%20summarises%20the%20work%20of%20more%20than%20100%20researchers%20worldwide%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20tax%20administrations.%20This%20work%20analyses%20new%20data%20on%20multinational%20companies%20(MNCs)%2C%20and%20the%20offshore%20wealth%20of%20households%2C%20and%20how%20policy%20initiatives%20of%20the%20last%20decade%20have%20impacted%20them.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20systematic%20attempt%20to%20analyse%20information%20available%20in%20the%20field%20of%20taxation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGabriel%20Zucman%2C%20co-author%20of%20the%20report%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CTax%20evasion%2C%20wealth%20concealment%2C%20profit%20shifting%20to%20tax%20havens%20are%20not%20laws%20of%20nature.%20They%20are%20the%20results%20of%20policy%20choices%20or%20of%20the%20failure%20to%20make%20certain%20choices.%20It%20is%20necessary%20to%20assess%20the%20consequences%20of%20policies%20enacted%20in%20this%20area%20and%20to%20investigate%20what%20else%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20improve%20the%20sustainability%20of%20our%20tax%20systems.%20There%20is%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20a%20need%20for%20an%20IPCC%20%5BIntergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%5D%20of%20taxation%20%E2%80%93%20and%20we%20hope%20to%20contribute%20to%20this%20evolution%20with%20this%20first-of-its-kind%20report.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20investigates%20the%20effects%20of%20international%20reforms%20adopted%20over%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fincometaxindia.gov.in%2FPages%2Feoi%2Fexchange-of-information.aspx%5C%22%3Eautomatic%20international%20exchange%20of%20bank%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20international%20agreement%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fglobal-corporate-minimum-tax-5192149%5C%22%3Eglobal%20minimum%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20MNCs%2C%20among%20other%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20automatic%20exchange%20of%20information%20was%20introduced%20in%202017%20to%20fight%20offshore%20tax%20evasion%20by%20wealthy%20individuals.%20In%202023%2C%20more%20than%20100%20countries%20exchanged%20information%20on%20the%20deposits%20of%20non-residents%20to%20foreign%20tax%20authorities%20as%20part%20of%20the%20common%20reporting%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20last%20year%2C%20India%20received%20the%20fourth%20set%20of%20Swiss%20bank%20account%20details%20of%20its%20nationals%20and%20organisations%20as%20part%20of%20this%20exchange.%C2%A0%20Switzerland%20has%20shared%20particulars%20of%20nearly%2034%20lakh%20financial%20accounts%20with%20101%20countries%20as%20part%20of%20this%20exchange%2C%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Findia-gets-4th-set-of-swiss-bank-account-details-under-automatic-info-exchange-framework%2Farticleshow%2F94762826.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20a%20group%20of%20136%20countries%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F5dc4e2d5-d7bd-4000-bf94-088f17e21936%5C%22%3Eincluding%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fminimum-global-tax-rate-of-15-136-nations-india-tax-havens%5C%22%3Eset%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20minimum%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Ffinance%2Fwhat-is-global-minimum-tax-deal-what-will-it-mean-2021-10-08%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20tax%20rate%20of%2015%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20MNCs%20and%20sought%20to%20make%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20avoid%20taxation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20number%20of%20loopholes%20are%20watering%20down%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20measures%2C%20says%20the%20Global%20Tax%20Evasion%20Report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsecret-irs-files-income-tax-avoid-buffett-bezos-musk-propublica%5C%22%3EHow%20Billionaires%20Like%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Warren%20Buffett%20Effectively%20Avoid%20Income%20Tax%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20findings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20offshore%20tax%20evasion%20by%20wealthy%20individuals%20has%20decreased%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20attributing%20it%20to%20the%20automatic%20exchange%20of%20bank%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20estimates%20that%20offshore%20tax%20evasion%20has%20diminished%20by%20a%20factor%20of%20about%20three%20over%20this%20period.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20one-third%20of%20its%20original%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%202013%2C%20households%20held%20the%20equivalent%20of%2010%25%20of%20world%20GDP%20in%20financial%20wealth%20in%20global%20tax%20havens%2C%20much%20of%20which%20was%20undeclared.%20Today%2C%20about%2025%25%20of%20this%20offshore%20wealth%20remains%20untaxed%2C%20marking%20a%20substantial%20reduction%20in%20non-compliance%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20however%2C%20highlights%20that%20offshore%20tax%20evasion%20still%20happens%20due%20to%20non-compliance%20by%20offshore%20financial%20institutions%20and%20limitations%20in%20the%20automatic%20exchange%20of%20bank%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20institutions%20adhere%20to%20reporting%20requirements%2C%20some%20do%20not%20due%20to%20fears%20of%20losing%20customers%20and%20lax%20enforcement%20by%20foreign%20tax%20authorities%2C%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20not%20all%20assets%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20automatic%20exchange%20of%20bank%20information%2C%20allowing%20individuals%20to%20exploit%20these%20gaps%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20it%20further%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20report%20finds%20a%20considerable%20amount%20of%20profit%20shifting%20to%20tax%20havens%2C%20with%20no%20apparent%20impact%20of%20policies%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EApproximately%20%241%20trillion%20was%20shifted%20to%20tax%20havens%20in%202022%2C%20equivalent%20to%2035%25%20of%20all%20profits%20booked%20by%20MNCs%20outside%20their%20headquarters%E2%80%99%20countries.%20This%20profit%20shifting%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20substantial%20loss%20of%20corporate%20tax%20revenues%20globally%2C%20nearly%2010%25%20of%20the%20total%20collected.%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUS%20multinationals%20are%20responsible%20for%20around%2040%25%20of%20this%20profit%20shifting%2C%20with%20Continental%20European%20countries%20being%20the%20most%20affected%20by%20this%20evasion%2C%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20weakening%20of%20the%20global%20minimum%20tax%20of%2015%25%20on%20multinationals%2C%20which%20had%20generated%20high%20expectations%20in%202021.%20It%20was%20initially%20anticipated%20to%20significantly%20increase%20global%20corporate%20tax%20revenues.%20However%2C%20several%20loopholes%20have%20reduced%20its%20expected%20impact%20by%20a%20factor%20of%203%2C%20as%20earlier%20mentioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20subsidies%20race%20for%20green-energy%20producers%20may%20outweigh%20the%20revenue%20gains%20generated%20by%20the%20global%20minimum%20corporate%20tax%2C%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20finds%20that%20global%20billionaires%20have%20effective%20tax%20rates%20equivalent%20to%200%25%20to%200.5%25%20of%20their%20wealth%20due%20to%20the%20frequent%20use%20of%20shell%20companies%20to%20avoid%20income%20taxation.%20Surprisingly%2C%20there%20have%20been%20no%20serious%20attempts%20to%20address%20this%20situation%2C%20which%20risks%20eroding%20the%20social%20acceptability%20of%20existing%20tax%20systems%2C%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20report%20highlights%20the%20emergence%20of%20new%20forms%20of%20aggressive%20tax%20competition%20that%20negatively%20affect%20government%20revenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20many%20countries%20have%20introduced%20preferential%20tax%20regimes%20aimed%20at%20attracting%20specific%20socio-economic%20groups%20perceived%20as%20particularly%20mobile.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20a%20single-country%20perspective%2C%20this%20strategy%C2%A0%20can%20enhance%20tax%20collection%20and%20boost%20domestic%20activity.%20But%20globally%20these%20policies%20are%20negative%20sum%3A%20taxpayers%20attracted%20by%20one%20country%20reduce%20the%20tax%20base%20by%20the%20same%20amount%20in%20another%2C%20and%20global%20tax%20revenue%20collection%20falls.%20Because%20the%20special%20regimes%20are%20primarily%20targeted%20to%20wealthy%20individuals%2C%20they%20reduce%20the%20progressivity%20of%20tax%20systems%2C%20fueling%20inequality.%20The%20tax-savings%20per%20beneficiary%20are%20high%20as%20are%20the%20fiscal%20costs%20for%20governments%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20findings%2C%20Zucman%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20like%20in%20Sergio%20Leone%E2%80%99s%20movie%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Good%2C%20the%20Bad%20and%20the%20Ugly%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Our%20research%20uncovers%20a%20major%20success%20worth%20celebrating%20%E2%80%93%20the%20end%20of%20bank%20secrecy%2C%20a%20setback%20%E2%80%93%20the%20dramatic%20weakening%20of%20the%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20MNCs%2C%20and%20issues%20that%20remain%20unaddressed%2C%20such%20as%20the%20persistently%20low%20effective%20tax%20rates%20of%20global%20billionaires.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-global-minimum-corporate-tax-debate-us-janet-yellen%5C%22%3EWhat%20Should%20India%E2%80%99s%20Response%20Be%20to%20the%20Global%20Minimum%20Corporate%20Tax%20Debate%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESolutions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20these%20challenges%2C%20the%20report%20proposes%20several%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20key%20proposal%20we%20consider%20in%20the%20report%20is%20to%20institute%20a%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20billionaires%2C%20equal%20to%202%25%20of%20their%20wealth%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Zucman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20logical%20next%20step%20after%20the%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20MNCs%20%E2%80%93%20which%20demonstrates%20that%20it%20is%20possible%20for%20countries%20to%20agree%20on%20minimum%20tax%20rates%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20understand%20the%20logic%20of%20this%20proposal%2C%20consider%20a%20billionaire%2C%20John%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20owns%20a%20stake%20in%20a%20company%20worth%20%2410%20billion.%20To%20simplify%2C%20assume%20that%20this%20%2410%20billion%20stake%20accounts%20for%20all%20his%20wealth.%20Any%20country%20could%20compute%20the%20tax%20deficit%20of%20John%2C%20namely%20the%20difference%20between%20what%20John%20pays%20in%20personal%20taxes%20today%20and%20what%20he%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20if%20he%20was%20subject%20to%20a%202%25%20minimum%20tax%20on%20wealth%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20if%20John%20pays%20%2450%20million%20in%20personal%20taxes%2C%20he%20has%20a%20tax%20deficit%20of%202%25%20times%20%2410%20billion%20minus%20%2450%20million%2C%20which%20is%20%24150%20million.%20Any%20country%20could%20then%20collect%20a%20portion%20of%20this%20tax%20deficit.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20the%20firm%20from%20which%20John%20derives%20his%20wealth%20makes%2010%25%20of%20its%20sales%20in%20India%2C%20then%20India%20could%20collect%2010%25%20of%20John%E2%80%99s%20tax%20deficit%2C%20i.e.%2C%20%2415%20million.%20The%20underlying%20logic%20is%20that%2010%25%20of%20John%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20(the%20value%20of%20the%20business%20he%20owns)%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20deriving%20from%20access%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20market.%20If%20no%20country%20ensures%20that%20John%20pays%20at%20least%202%25%20of%20his%20wealth%20in%20taxes%2C%20some%20countries%20need%20to%20step%20in%20and%20play%20the%20role%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctax%20collector%20of%20last%20resort%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20it%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20US%20resident%20owns%20real%20estate%20in%20India%20(or%20business%20property%20like%20commercial%20real%20estate)%2C%20then%20India%20already%20taxes%20this%20wealth%20today.%20The%20mechanism%20we%20describe%20here%20is%20simply%20an%20extension%20of%20this%20long-standing%20practice%20to%20all%20other%20forms%20of%20wealth%20beyond%20tangible%20properties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20report%20calls%20for%20strengthening%20of%20the%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20MNCs%2C%20and%20ensure%20it%20is%20free%20of%20loopholes.%20This%2C%20it%20believes%2C%20could%20raise%20an%20additional%20%24250%20billion%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIncreasing%20the%20minimum%20tax%20to%2020%25%20leads%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20revenue%20by%20a%20factor%20of%201.75%20relative%20to%20a%20minimum%20tax%20rate%20of%2015%25.%20With%20a%20minimum%20rate%20of%2025%25%2C%20the%20revenues%20nearly%20triple.%20With%20a%20minimum%20rate%20of%2030%25%20they%20almost%20quadruple%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20allocate%20these%20additional%20revenues%20to%20specific%20countries%2C%20we%20consider%20two%20polar%20cases%3A%20full%20collection%20of%20the%20minimum%20tax%20by%20headquarter%20countries%20and%20full%20collection%20by%20host%20countries.%20Where%20the%20revenues%20end%20up%20depends%20on%20whether%20host%20countries%20will%20implement%20minimum%20taxes.%20If%20they%20do%20not%2C%20headquarter%20countries%20will%20reap%20the%20benefits.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20country-level%20results%20should%20be%20interpreted%20with%20care.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698032622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F17155644%2Fimage-1399.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnew-report-calls-for-global-minimum-tax-on-billionaires-says-offshore-tax-evasion-has-decreased%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%2C%20however%2C%20highlights%20that%20offshore%20tax%20evasion%20still%20happens%20due%20to%20non-compliance%20by%20offshore%20financial%20institutions%20and%20limitations%20in%20the%20automatic%20exchange%20of%20bank%20information.%20It%20calls%20for%20the%20strengthening%20of%20the%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20MNCs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnew-report-calls-for-global-minimum-tax-on-billionaires-says-offshore-t