Sharif%20with%20his%20family%20at%20the%20rally%20in%20Lahore%2C%20October%2021.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40pmln_org%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20known%20to%20be%20a%20man%20of%20many%20words%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20does%20have%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20with%20his%20followers.%20And%20the%20primary%20thing%20he%20did%20from%20the%20podium%20was%20to%20engage%20and%20renew%20a%20bond%20with%20his%20devotees.%20He%20made%20economic%20recovery%20the%20centrepiece%20of%20his%20narrative%20reset%20by%20comparing%20the%20relative%20prosperity%20during%20his%202013-2017%20era%20when%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20growth%20rate%20was%205.8%25%20and%20inflation%20at%20around%204%25%20with%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20stint.%20Sharif%20invoked%20mega%20projects%20he%20had%20commissioned%20and%20completed%20over%20his%20previous%20terms%20and%20his%20reputation%20for%20growth%20and%20development.%20He%20clearly%20attempted%20to%20put%20himself%20between%20the%20electorate%20and%20the%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20government%E2%80%99s%20abysmal%20performance%20%E2%80%93%20its%20various%20constraints%20notwithstanding%20%E2%80%93%20during%20which%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FEconomy%2FInflation%2FPakistan-inflation-hits-record-35-as-IMF-talks-drag-on%5C%22%3Einflation%20had%20risen%20to%2035%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Pakistan%20narrowly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-12%2Fpakistan-secures-final-imf-approval-for-3-billion-bailout%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3Edodged%20the%20economic%20default%20bullet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20he%20bragged%20about%20making%20Pakistan%20a%20declared%20nuclear-weapons%20state%2C%20he%20also%20reiterated%20%E2%80%93%20without%20naming%20India%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20can%20be%20no%20progress%20while%20fighting%20the%20neighbours.%20For%20a%20first%20rally%20and%20speech%20after%20a%20four-year%20interregnum%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20did%20what%20he%20had%20set%20out%20to%20do%3A%20energise%20and%20mobilise%20his%20base%2C%20especially%20the%20Punjab.%20But%20the%20nostalgic%20broad%20strokes%20and%20reconciliatory%20notes%20can%20only%20be%20used%20a%20few%20times%20before%20they%20run%20out%20of%20their%20political%20efficacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENawaz%20Sharif%20will%20have%20to%20tackle%20both%20the%20economic%20and%20political%20future%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20define%20and%20refine%20the%20roadmap%2C%20if%20he%20has%20any.%20While%20he%20did%20not%20name%20Imran%20Khan%20even%20once%20in%20his%20speech%2C%20it%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20he%20addresses%20the%20issue%20of%20his%20arch%20rival%E2%80%99s%20incarceration%20and%20potential%20elimination%20from%20the%20next%20elections.%20An%20election%20held%20without%20Imran%20Khan%20would%20be%20as%20tainted%20as%20the%20one%20that%20was%20held%20without%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20in%202018.%20While%20the%20PML-N%20has%20fielded%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20effectively%20as%20its%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%2C%20were%20it%20to%20prevail%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1782740%2Fnawaz-moves-to-restore-appeals-against-convictions%5C%22%3Elegal%20status%20of%20his%20previous%20disqualification%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20process%20is%20still%20not%20completely%20clear.%20But%20all%20indications%20are%20that%20the%20army%20would%20not%20create%20any%20hurdles%20in%20his%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20one%20speech%20is%20not%20much%20to%20go%20by%2C%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20do%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20bidding%20were%20he%20to%20return%20to%20power%20a%20fourth%20time.%20Opting%20for%20reticence%20and%20restraint%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20former%20generals%20and%20judges%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20tactical%20move%20on%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20part.%20With%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20encroachment%20over%20the%20political%20domain%20it%20is%20more%20likely%20than%20ever%20before%20that%20a%20PM%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20eventually%20lock%20horns%20with%20an%20army%20chief%2C%20whether%20the%20incumbent%20or%20a%20successor.%20It%20is%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20principals%2C%20positions%2C%20and%20politics%20that%20define%20the%20interplay%20between%20the%20PMs%20and%20the%20army%20chiefs%20in%20Pakistan.%20Militaries%20are%20not%20trained%20to%20run%20complex%20states%20and%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20even%20a%20weak%20one%20like%20Pakistan%E2%80%94puts%20the%20brass%20at%20loggerheads%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3Ede%20jure%3C%2Fem%3E%20chief%20executives.%20The%20historical%20lesson%20is%20that%20even%20the%20weakest%20prime%20ministers%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1988-05-30-mn-2462-story.html%5C%22%3EMuhammad%20Khan%20Junejo%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F2004%2F06%2F27%2Fpakistani-premier-forced-out-in-favor-of-finance-minister%2F68680c3c-3c33-4e2e-995f-d3742dac01f0%2F%5C%22%3EMir%20Zafarullah%20Khan%20Jamali%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended%20up%20having%20differences%20with%20the%20strongest%20army%20dictators%2C%20General%20Ziaul%20Haq%20and%20General%20Musharraf%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENawaz%20Sharif%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20cut%20from%20a%20very%20different%20cloth.%20He%20had%20tried%20to%20assert%20his%20constitutional%20authority%20every%20single%20time%20he%20occupied%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20in%20the%20past%2C%20though%20at%20his%20personal%20and%20political%20peril.%20And%20there%20is%20little%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20would%20be%20different%20this%20time%20around.%20What%20he%20does%20to%20avert%20an%20outcome%20like%20the%20previous%20ones%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see.%20The%20army%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20conundrum%20and%20will%20likely%20use%20PTI%E2%80%99s%20breakaway%20factions%20and%20other%20levers%20to%20keep%20in%20check%20Nawaz%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20prospects%20at%20the%20polls%20and%20thereafter.%20With%20eyes%20on%20his%20political%20legacy%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20has%20always%20wanted%20to%20go%20down%20in%20history%20as%20a%20statesman%20who%20decisively%20upended%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20hegemony%20over%20politics%20and%20governance%20in%20Pakistan.%20He%20has%20returned%20to%20Pakistan%20that%20has%20regressed%20to%20a%20full-blown%20praetorian%20state.%20Sharif%20has%20an%20uphill%20battle%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fmohammad-taqi%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMohammad%20Taqi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Pakistani-American%20columnist.%20He%20tweets%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmazdaki%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%40mazdaki%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698030106000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F23082858%2FF8-EOQpaAAEgVSK.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnawaz-sharif-faces-an-uphill-battle-upon-return-to-pakistan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20have%20to%20tackle%20both%20the%20economic%20and%20political%20future%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20define%20and%20refine%20the%20roadmap%2C%20if%20he%20has%20any.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnawaz-sharif-faces-an-uphill-battle-upon-return-to-pakistan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20drug%20lord%20supplied%20cocaine%20to%20Mumbai%20parties%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698029649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104642818%2Cimgsize-24154.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fsupplied-cocaine-to-mumbai-parties%2Farticleshow%2F104638032.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22T